  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: PROCEDURE (OPCS) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
      <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_procedure__opcs_">PROCEDURE (OPCS)</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_clinical_classification_code">CLINICAL CLASSIFICATION CODE</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
      <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_procedure__opcs_">PROCEDURE (OPCS)</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_patient_procedure">Patient Procedure</xref>
 other than the 
              <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_primary_procedure__opcs_">PRIMARY PROCEDURE (OPCS)</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
For 
              <xref href="https://v3.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/navigation/commissioning_data_sets_menu.html" scope="external" format="html">Commissioning Data Sets</xref>
 purposes it is recommended that multiple 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_patient_procedure">Patient Procedures</xref>
 are recorded and the CDS XML Schema (CDS Version 6 onwards) has been designed to carry as many 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_patient_procedure">Patient Procedures</xref>
 as required.        </p>
  </div>
